modules.description: This module converts identifiers between Pascal, Camel, Snake, and Kebab case formats. It operates on string inputs representing variable or function names, transforming them to match different naming conventions used in code generation and parsing tasks. For example, it can convert `"JohnDoe"` to `"john_doe"` or `"john-doe"` as needed when generating code in languages with specific case requirements.

This module converts identifiers between Pascal, Camel, Snake, and Kebab case formats. It operates on strings representing variable or function names, enabling transformations required when generating or parsing code across languages with different naming conventions. Use it to adapt identifiers during code generation for languages like Python, JavaScript, or Rust.
